main event: Multiple civilian and military observers reported seeing a whitish-yellow unidentified object with trails of sparks in the Phoenix, Arizona area on August 16, 1965.
interesting points: Reports came from a large number of civilians and military personnel,The object was described as a very bright single object,Some reports noted a trail of white flame with sparks behind it,The average observation time was about 10 seconds,The object's movement was reported differently by ground and airborne observers.
sighted object: whitish-yellow unidentified object with trails of sparks
witness description: civilians and military personnel in the Phoenix area
